<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-223] columnNames field of @Index annotation is ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-223</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like we completely ignore the &quot;columnNames&quot; field of the org.apache.openjpa.persistence.jdbc.Index annotation. From Jonathan Feinberg on the mailing list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there any way to cause the OpenJPA schema builder to emit an index across multiple columns? My attempt,&lt;br/&gt;
 @Column(columnDefinition = &quot;bytea&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
 @Index(name = &quot;i_owner_md5&quot;, columnNames = &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;owner_id, md5&quot; }
&lt;p&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 public byte[] getMd5()&lt;/p&gt;
 {
  return md5;
 }

&lt;p&gt;is silently misinterpreted, in that only the annotated field (md5) gets indexed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
